<div align="center" style="display:none;" id="div_ipcheck">
    <form name="IPForm" method="post" action="">
        <table width="95%" class="table">
            <tr>
                <td class="subHeader" colspan="2">User IP Check</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td colspan="2" style="border-bottom:1px solid #000000;">
                    Using this panel you can check up on the registration IP and last IP of users.<br>
                    Remember, sometimes large groups of people legitimately one IP.<br>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="row1">
                <td width="227">Username</td>
                <td width="271">
                    <input type="text" class="textfield" name="ip_username" id="ip_username" />
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="row2">
                <td>User ID</td>
                <td>
                    <input type="text" class="textfield" name="ip_userid" id="ip_userid" />
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="row1">
                <td>IP Address (Broken)</td>
                <td>
                    <input type="text" class="textfield" name="ip_address" id="ip_address" />
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td colspan="2" style="border-top:1px solid #000000;">
                    <input type="submit" name="Check_IP" id="ip_check_search" value="Run Search">
                </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
    </form>
</div>